Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy, Mr Gwede Mantashe has been hospitalised due to Covid-19. This is after he and his wife, Nolwandle Mantashe tested positive for COVID-19 about a week ago. In a statement from the Presidency, it was confirmed that Mantashe was admitted to hospital on the advice of their family doctor for better medical attention and monitoring, whilst his wife will continue to self-quarantine at their home. ALSO READ:Â GWEDE MANTASHE TESTS POSITIVE FOR COVID-19 "We will continue to give the Mantashe family all the support they need during this time. We wish both Minister and Mrs Mantashe a speedy recovery from this invisible enemy and we are quite confident that they will emerge victorious against the coronavirus," said the Presidency. Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy, Mr Gwede Mantashe, has been admitted to hospital on the advice of the family doctor for better medical attention and monitoring after testing positive for Covid-19 last week. https://t.co/y2x98EONEk  